.TH history-prune 1  "history-prune " 
.SH NAME
history\-prune \- Prune or compact run history according to a retention policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBhistory\-prune\fR [\fB\-\-max\-records\fR] [\fB\-\-max\-age\-days\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prune or compact run history according to a retention policy
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-records\fR \fI<COUNT>\fR
Keep only the N most\-recent records
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-age\-days\fR \fI<DAYS>\fR
Drop records older than N days
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Print what would be removed without actually deleting anything
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
